More delays in the Nathaniel Julies case. The trial will now start afresh after the untimely passing of Judge Ramarumo Monama. eNCA's Nqobile Madlala was in court and has an update. #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - More delays in the Nathaniel Julies case. His family says the wheels of justice are turning slowly. READ: Nathaniel Julies murder case postponed to June The trial will now start afresh after the untimely passing of Judge Ramarumo Monama. Julies was allegedly shot by three officers in August 2020 in Eldorado Park. READ: Nathaniel Julies case: Pre-trial hearing begins His mother Bridget Harris said the case is putting strain on the family. "We were just hoping we can start where we end off...  but unfortunately it didn't work out that way," she said. The pre-trial has now been postponed to 3 June.